The undersigned, *#FIRST_NAME_EN #LAST_NAME_EN*, born on #BIRTH_DATE, citizen of #CITIZENSHIP_EN, holder of 
a #PASSPORT_EN No. #PASSPORT_NR, hereinafter referred to as the SOLE OWNER, I adopt the following Incorporation act:

Art. 1. With this Incorporation act, a single-member limited liability company (the Company) is formed. The company 
is a legal entity that is not responsible for the obligations of the sole owner.

Art. 2. The name of the Company is *"#COMPANY_NAME_BG" ЕООД*, which is written in Latin as follows: 
*"#COMPANY_NAME_EN" LTD*.

#v(1em)

Art. 3. The seat and address of management of the company is: #ADDRESS_EN, and e-mail address: #EMAIL_MGT. 
Address for correspondence with NRA: #ADDRESS_EN, and e-mail address: #EMAIL_FIN.

#v(1em)

Art. 4. The Company shall not be limited by a term or other termination condition.

#v(1em)

Art. 5. The subject of activity of the company is: 

- computer programming (КИД-2025 62.10);
- information technology consultancy activities and management and operation of computer facilities (КИД-2025 62.20);
- other information technology activities (КИД-2025 62.90).

#v(1em)

Art. 6. By decision of the Sole Owner, the Company may:

- to establish branches of the company both in the country and abroad;
- to participate in various associations of commercial companies, consortia, holdings, etc.;
- to be transferred through a transaction as a set of rights, obligations and factual relations.

Art. 7. The sole owner of the capital is #FIRST_NAME_EN #LAST_NAME_EN.

#v(1em)

Art. 8. The capital of the company is in the amount of EUR #CAPITAL /three hundred/, which consists of #SHARES /#SHARES_EN/ 
company shares, with a nominal value of EUR #NOMINAL /#NOMINAL_EN/ for each share. The shares of the company are indivisible. 
All #SHARES /#SHARES_EN/ shares are owned by #FIRST_NAME_EN #LAST_NAME_EN, born on #BIRTH_DATE, citizen of #CITIZENSHIP_EN, holder 
of a #PASSPORT_EN No. #PASSPORT_NR, issued on #PASSPORT_ISSUED, valid until #PASSPORT_VALID. At the time of the 
company's entry in the Commercial Register at the Registry Agency, the capital was paid entirely by the sole owner.

#v(1em)

Art. 9. The capital of the Company may be increased by:

- increase of shares;
- subscription of new shares;
- admission of new partners.

#v(1em)

Art. 10. (1) The reduction of the capital may be made by a decision of the Sole Owner in compliance with the requirements 
of the law. The decision shall specify the purpose of the reduction, its amount and the manner in which it will be 
implemented.

(2) The capital may not be reduced below EUR 2 (two) and the value of one unit may not be less than EUR 1 (one).

#v(1em)

Art. 11. (1) The company share may be transferred and inherited.

(2) The transfer of the company share shall be made with notarized signatures and content of the contract and shall be 
entered in the Commercial Register.

#v(1em)

Art. 12. In the event of a transfer of a share, the successor shall be jointly and severally liable with his predecessor 
for the contributions due at the time of the transfer against the share of the capital.

#v(1em)

Art. 13. A new shareholder shall be admitted upon his/her written application, in which he/she declares that he/she 
accepts the terms of the articles of association.

#v(1em)

Art. 14. The sole owner shall have the right to:

- To participate in the management of the company;
- To participate in the distribution of profits;
- To be informed about the progress of company affairs, in person or through Proxy;
- To review at any time the company's papers and to obtain a copy of them;
- To receive a dividend;
- To receive a liquidation share.

#v(1em)

Art. 15. The sole owner shall be obliged:

- To pay or pay his/her share or additional contribution, according to the specified deadlines;
- To participate in the work of the company and to assist the company in carrying out its activities.

#v(1em)

Art. 16. The sole owner shall be responsible for the obligations of the company with his share contribution to the 
capital of the company.

#v(1em)

Art. 17. The sole owner may be represented by a proxy with an explicit notarized power of attorney.

Art. 18. The sole owner may not claim a real share of the company's property while the same exists.

Art. 19. (1) The bodies of the company shall be:

- the sole owner;
- manager (managers).

(2) The manager may not be a shareholder.

#v(1em)

Art. 20. (1) The sole owner shall be the supreme body of the company and may take decisions on all issues of its activity.

(2) The Manager shall participate in the meetings of the Sole Owner with an advisory vote, if he is not a shareholder.

(3) When the persons employed in the company are more than 50, they shall be represented in the meetings of the 
Sole Owner with an advisory vote.

#v(1em)

Art. 21. (1) The sole owner shall have exclusive competence to adopt decisions regarding:

- amendment and supplementation of this Constituent Act;
- admission of new partners;
- adoption of the annual report and balance sheet, distribution of profit and making decisions on its payment;
- increase and decrease of the share capital;
- election of the manager, determination of his/her remuneration and release from liability;
- decision-making for opening and closing branches and participation in other companies;
- decision-making for acquisition and expropriation of immovable property and rights in rem thereto;
- taking decisions for filing claims of the company against the manager or controller and appointing a representative 
to conduct proceedings against them;
- termination of the activity of the company or for its transformation, as well as its transfer through a transaction;
- election of a controller;
- payment of additional cash contributions, the term and manner of their payment;
- appointment of liquidators of the company.

#v(1em)

Art. 22. (1) Minutes shall be kept for each meeting of the sole owner, which shall reflect the discussions made and 
the decisions taken.

(2) Copies and extracts from the minutes shall be issued by the Manager.

(3) The minutes book shall be kept by the manager.

#v(1em)

Art. 23. (1) The decisions of the Sole Owner, which relate to the entries under Art. 119, para. 2 of the Commerce Act, 
must be entered in the Commercial Register.

(2) The decisions on amendment and supplementation of the Constituent Act and termination of the company shall enter 
into force after their entry in the Commercial Register.

(3) Increase and decrease of the capital, admission and exclusion of a shareholder, transformation of the company, 
election and dismissal of a manager, as well as appointment of a liquidator shall have effect from their entry in the 
Commercial Register.

#v(1em)

Art. 24. (1) The manager shall have all rights and obligations in accordance with the requirements of the law.

(2) The manager shall organize and manage the overall economic activity of the company. He resolves all issues related 
to the subject of activity of the company, except for the issues that by law or under this contract are within the 
exclusive competence of the Sole Owner.

(3) The manager may not be a shareholder. If he is not a shareholder, he bears full property responsibility for the 
damages caused to the company, including lost profits. The manager shall be remunerated by decision of the Sole Owner.

#v(1em)

Art. 25. (1) The company shall be represented by the manager. The name of the manager shall be entered in the Commercial 
Register, who shall submit a notarized consent with a specimen of the signature. When appointing more than one manager, 
the Sole Owner of the capital determines the manner in which the managers represent the Company before third parties.

(2) The power of attorney of the manager may be revoked at any time and his/her name may be deleted from the Commercial 
Register.

(3) The manager may request to be deleted from the Commercial Register with a written notification to the company. 
Within one month after receiving the notification, the company must apply for its exemption in the Commercial Register. 
If the company fails to do so, the manager may himself apply for registration of this circumstance, which is entered, 
regardless of whether another person has been elected in his place.

(4) The authorization and its deletion shall have effect in relation to third parties in good faith after their 
registration.

(5) The relations between the company and the manager shall be regulated by a contract for assignment of management. 
The contract is concluded in writing on behalf of the company through a person authorized by the sole owner.

#v(1em)

Art. 26. (1) Without the consent of the company, the manager shall not have the right:

- to carry out commercial transactions on its own behalf or on behalf of others;
- to participate in general partnerships, limited partnerships and limited liability companies;
- to hold a position in the management bodies of other companies.

(2) The restrictions under Para. 1 shall apply when an activity similar to that of the company is carried out.

(3) In case of violation of the obligations under Para. 1, the manager shall owe compensation for the damages caused to 
the company.

#v(1em)

Art. 27. (1) The company shall keep a book of shares and a protocol book for the decisions of the sole owner.

(2) The manager shall be responsible for the regular keeping of the company books.

#v(1em)

Art. 28. The company shall be terminated:

- upon expiry of the term specified in the Constituent Act;
- by decision of the Sole Owner;
- by merging and merging into a joint-stock company or other limited liability company;
- upon declaration of bankruptcy;
- by a court decision in cases provided for by the Commerce Act.

#v(1em)

Art. 29. (1) Upon termination of the company on the grounds of Art. 154, items 1, 2 and 5 and Art. 155 of the Commerce 
Act, liquidation proceedings are initiated.

(2) The liquidator of the company shall be the manager, unless another person has been appointed by the contract or by 
a decision of the sole owner.

(3) The liquidation of the company shall be carried out in accordance with Chapter Seventeen of the Commerce Act.

#v(1em)

§ 1. For the issues not regulated in this Constituent Act, the laws of the Republic of Bulgaria shall apply.

§ 2. This Incorporation act was adopted on 11.10.2024 by a decision of the sole owner of the capital.
